org.fcrepo.http.commons.utils

Interface UncheckedBiConsumer<S,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of the first argument to the operation
    T - the type of the second argument to the operation
    All Superinterfaces:
    BiConsumer<S,T>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface UncheckedBiConsumer<S,T>
extends BiConsumer<S,T>
    It is sometimes convenient to use an operation that throws checked exceptions inside of a functional incantation. This type permits that. It should be used with great caution! Only uncheck exceptions for which no reasonable recovery is available.
    Author:
    ajs6f
